that every part of your being

26:18.342 --> 26:19.691
is devoted to them.

26:19.822 --> 26:20.866
How the fuck I do that?

26:20.997 --> 26:22.303
I don't know, nigga.

26:22.433 --> 26:23.565
Make her a slow jams tape
or some shit.

26:23.695 --> 26:24.870
You know bitches love music.

26:25.001 --> 26:26.611
The point is, man,

26:26.742 --> 26:28.352
you just gotta convince her
about how you really feel.

26:28.483 --> 26:31.442
[R&B music plays]

26:31.573 --> 26:33.575
Excuse me, ma'am.
You have a pen I can borrow?

26:33.705 --> 26:34.793
What you doing, man?

26:37.187 --> 26:40.451
Thank you. Appreciate it.

26:40.582 --> 26:42.410
Man, what you about to do,
draw a picture?

26:43.498 --> 26:45.804
Smooth talking.

26:47.850 --> 26:50.548
[tense music plays]

26:50.679 --> 26:51.636
[woman] You ready?

26:51.767 --> 26:53.247
[man] I can handle this shit.

26:53.377 --> 26:55.162
Nigga, I know none of y'all
ain't scared.

26:55.292 --> 26:56.990
Yo!

26:57.120 --> 26:58.426
Fuck y'all doing
standing around

26:58.556 --> 26:59.818
looking like dicks
without balls?

27:01.211 --> 27:02.299
Why Meech ain't pop Jay Mo?

27:02.430 --> 27:03.997
Hey.

27:04.127 --> 27:05.433
I heard he tried
to make a deal with Filmel.

27:05.563 --> 27:07.174
What's up with that?

27:07.304 --> 27:08.392
That ain't something
for y'all to be questioning.

27:08.523 --> 27:10.003
I'm just saying.

27:10.133 --> 27:11.526
If the nigga ain't gon' ride
for his own brother,

27:11.656 --> 27:12.614
-why would he do it for us?
-[man] Right.

27:12.744 --> 27:14.050
Because we paying y'all.

27:14.181 --> 27:15.834
Now get y'all monkey asses
back on the post

27:15.965 --> 27:17.053
before I kick both
of y'all asses.

27:17.184 --> 27:19.708
And look.
I know how y'all feel.

27:19.838 --> 27:21.710
But what if Jay Mo ain't do it?

27:21.840 --> 27:23.190
Meech kills him
and start a war.

27:23.320 --> 27:24.495
How many of y'all
willing to stand

27:24.626 --> 27:26.019
on hot blocks
for the wrong dude?

27:26.149 --> 27:28.456
Armageddon's already started.

27:28.586 --> 27:30.762
Those 12th Street niggas
are walking around strapped,

27:30.893 --> 27:34.114
on high alert,
expecting us to clap back, man.

27:34.244 --> 27:36.507
Meech don't want us taking
no unnecessary shots.

27:36.638 --> 27:38.770
Now, Kato, you know
I ain't scared of shit.

27:38.901 --> 27:40.598
We ain't neither.

27:40.729 --> 27:42.252
But that don't mean
we want to get in a shootout.

27:42.383 --> 27:44.472
Hey, hey, hey, one thing
I know about this nigga Meech,

27:44.602 --> 27:45.995
he's thinking about shit
I ain't never thought about.

27:46.126 --> 27:47.997
So if he ain't taken
Jay Mo ass out,

27:48.128 --> 27:50.739
he for damn sure has a reason.

27:50.869 --> 27:53.002
When is the last time
either of you seen Meech

27:53.133 --> 27:56.005
or Tee not have our backs?

27:56.136 --> 27:57.746
Then continue
to play your position,

27:57.876 --> 27:59.269
and we gon' play ours.

27:59.400 --> 28:00.575
All right.

28:00.705 --> 28:01.967
Y'all better figure
this shit out.

28:02.098 --> 28:03.882
[tense music plays]

28:04.013 --> 28:05.319
Hey, get y'all asses up.

28:07.930 --> 28:10.019
Shit, nice teamwork.

28:10.150 --> 28:12.369
All day, but that shit
ain't gon' last.

28:12.543 --> 28:14.676
♪ ♪

28:14.806 --> 28:16.243
I just did that.

28:23.511 --> 28:24.816
What's going on?

28:24.947 --> 28:27.515
Terry's got an infection.

28:27.645 --> 28:29.299
They're worried it moved
into his brain.

28:29.430 --> 28:30.996
[Charles] If you cared,

28:31.127 --> 28:32.389
you would have been here
instead of out in them streets.

28:32.520 --> 28:33.999
Pops, it's not my fault,
all right?

28:34.130 --> 28:35.914
Somebody tried to jack him.

28:36.045 --> 28:38.613
Is that why your drug-dealing
goons been following us around?

28:38.743 --> 28:41.442
What?
You didn't think we'd notice?

28:41.572 --> 28:43.966
He's here now, baby.
That's all that matters.

28:44.097 --> 28:47.012
[phone ringing]

28:47.143 --> 28:49.885
[suspenseful music plays]

28:50.059 --> 28:53.106
♪ ♪

28:55.934 --> 28:57.545
What up doe?

28:57.675 --> 28:58.981
[Sockie] Nicole out here

28:59.112 --> 29:01.070
venturing in 12th Street
territory, man.

29:01.201 --> 29:02.202
What the fuck
you talking about, man?

29:02.332 --> 29:03.551
She 'posed to be next door.

29:03.681 --> 29:05.292
[Sockie] Yeah, well,

29:05.422 --> 29:07.859
I just seen her come out
the arcade off of Visger.

29:07.990 --> 29:09.252
All right, bet. I'm on my way.

29:11.646 --> 29:14.388
On your way where?

29:14.518 --> 29:15.867
You just got here.

29:15.998 --> 29:18.479
Ma, look, I'm just making
a quick run, a'ight?

29:18.609 --> 29:20.176
I'll be right back.
This is important.

29:20.307 --> 29:22.135
What's more important
than your own flesh and blood?

29:25.181 --> 29:27.662
[Lucille] Demetrius,
don't do this.

29:27.792 --> 29:29.011
Demetrius.

29:32.188 --> 29:34.364
[siren wailing in distance]

29:34.495 --> 29:36.105
[B-Mickie] Hey.
Hey, look, we got a problem.

29:36.236 --> 29:37.715
Deal with it.
I got a bigger one.

29:37.846 --> 29:39.413
Bruh, deal with it?
I'm talking dissension, dawg.

29:39.543 --> 29:42.155
That shit you did,
going to Filmel, it look weak.

29:42.285 --> 29:45.158
Man, I don't give a fuck
how it look.

29:45.288 --> 29:47.203
Nigga,
we need to dead Jay Mo ass.

29:47.334 --> 29:48.509
Nigga, you don't even
for sure know

29:48.639 --> 29:50.163
if that nigga
shot my brother, man.

29:50.293 --> 29:52.426
Nigga, it's the fact
that niggas think that he did.

29:52.556 --> 29:53.514
You gotta respond.

29:55.603 --> 29:57.692
You see,
gun-happy niggas like you

29:57.822 --> 30:00.521
is the reason real playas
always getting knocked, nigga.

30:00.651 --> 30:03.524
I ain't doing a motherfucking
thing until I get the truth.

30:03.654 --> 30:06.614
[tense music plays]

30:06.744 --> 30:10.357
What happened to that
King of Detroit shit, huh?

30:10.487 --> 30:11.793
Show me a king
that never dropped a body

30:11.923 --> 30:13.316
on the way to the throne.

30:13.490 --> 30:15.275
♪ ♪

30:15.405 --> 30:17.102
Nigga, I know for a fact,

30:17.233 --> 30:18.843
if somebody shot my brother,

30:18.974 --> 30:20.410
I'd been scorched the earth by
now.

30:20.541 --> 30:22.107
Oh, yeah?

30:22.238 --> 30:24.414
Well luckily,
Tee ain't your brother.

30:24.545 --> 30:26.851
Now do what I fucking said.

30:26.982 --> 30:29.637
[siren wailing in distance]

30:29.767 --> 30:32.683
[dramatic music plays]

30:32.814 --> 30:36.034
[doctor] Terry is out
of surgery and resting,

30:36.165 --> 30:37.862
and we cleaned out
the infection,

30:37.993 --> 30:39.342
but we can't say how well

30:39.473 --> 30:41.475
his eye is going to heal
right now.

30:41.605 --> 30:43.955
Are-are you saying that my son
might lose his vision?

30:44.086 --> 30:45.392
There's just no way

30:45.522 --> 30:46.871
to determine anything
at the moment.

30:47.002 --> 30:48.612
[Charles] How the hell
did that happen?

30:48.743 --> 30:50.135
His vision was fine
before he went back in

30:50.266 --> 30:51.311
for the second surgery.

30:52.790 --> 30:54.096
Somebody messed up?

30:55.489 --> 30:58.622
No procedure is without risk.

30:58.753 --> 31:01.321
But we always strive to give
our patients the best care.

31:01.451 --> 31:03.236
Did you make a mistake?

31:05.325 --> 31:07.196
I'm sorry. I can't answer that.

31:07.327 --> 31:08.676
[phone ringing in distance]

31:10.852 --> 31:13.246
If my son is seeing
anything other than 20/20

31:13.376 --> 31:16.031
when this is done,

31:16.161 --> 31:17.467
you're looking at a lawsuit.

31:21.863 --> 31:24.953
Mrs. Flenory, we're going
to do everything we can.

31:25.083 --> 31:26.737
You better.

31:26.868 --> 31:29.784
-[intercom beeps]
-[woman speaking indistinctly]

31:29.914 --> 31:32.265
[babies fussing]

31:47.018 --> 31:48.455
How'd you know I'd be here?

31:50.718 --> 31:53.503
We been in this hospital
three times.

31:53.634 --> 31:56.201
And every time,
this is your favorite place,

31:56.332 --> 31:58.682
staring at the newborns,

31:58.813 --> 32:02.033
thanking the Lord
and marveling at his handiwork.

32:05.994 --> 32:08.518
They so innocent
when they come into this world.

32:08.649 --> 32:11.391
Nothing we can do
can keep them that way.

32:11.521 --> 32:13.218
If something happens
to Terry's sight...

32:13.349 --> 32:14.611
The Lord will provide.

32:15.656 --> 32:16.526
How?

32:18.136 --> 32:19.921
Terry ain't gon' learn piano,
write music,

32:20.051 --> 32:20.965
and sign with Motown.

32:21.096 --> 32:22.184
No.

32:22.315 --> 32:23.664
But he is alive.

32:23.794 --> 32:26.493
And what right do we have
to ask for more?

32:26.623 --> 32:28.495
We have a right
to stop losing, Lucille.

32:29.800 --> 32:31.062
Money.

32:31.193 --> 32:32.673
Control of our kids.

32:34.109 --> 32:36.198
Our job is to protect them,
and we ain't been doing that.

32:37.808 --> 32:39.244
When Meech dropped out
to sell drugs,

32:39.375 --> 32:40.333
I said put him out.

32:41.551 --> 32:42.944
When we found that damn gun,

32:43.074 --> 32:44.206
I said he got to go.

32:45.294 --> 32:46.904
And now Terry lying up in here

32:47.035 --> 32:48.863
with a gunshot to his head,

32:48.993 --> 32:51.387
maybe going blind,
all because his brother,

32:51.518 --> 32:54.477
who I believe
pulled him into this.

32:54.608 --> 32:57.088
But you refuse
to make the hard choice.

32:57.219 --> 32:59.352
Terry ain't dealing drugs,
Charles.

32:59.482 --> 33:01.136
You need to let Meech go.

33:01.266 --> 33:02.920
[dramatic music plays]

33:03.051 --> 33:05.401
Drugs are polluting our home.
They killing us.

33:05.532 --> 33:07.882
And you and I ain't never
even touched a drop.

33:08.012 --> 33:11.102
I got one son
who just cheated death.

33:11.233 --> 33:13.278
And we put Demetrius out,

33:13.409 --> 33:16.499
if something happens to him,
how do I live with myself?

33:16.630 --> 33:18.849
What if something happens
to Nicole?

33:19.023 --> 33:22.113
♪ ♪

33:22.853 --> 33:24.768
Or us?

33:26.553 --> 33:28.511
How you gon' live
with yourself then?

33:36.214 --> 33:39.217
[babies crying]

33:46.964 --> 33:48.313
You wrote all these?

33:48.444 --> 33:51.012
Yeah, in the hospital.

33:51.142 --> 33:53.623
Well, why you just now
giving them to me?

33:53.754 --> 33:55.625
'Cause I wanted Zo to know

33:55.756 --> 33:57.888
that I was trying
to get better.

33:58.019 --> 34:00.674
And I hated myself
for abandoning y'all, you know?

34:00.804 --> 34:04.242
So those letters were what
kept me going in that place.

34:05.679 --> 34:06.810
Look, nigga, if you trying
to make me feel bad for you...

34:06.941 --> 34:08.203
Mo, come on.

34:08.333 --> 34:09.770
I don't want your pity,
all right?

34:12.468 --> 34:14.035
Look, you're Zoe's mother.

34:14.165 --> 34:15.253
I was out of line,

34:15.384 --> 34:17.647
and I'm saying that I'm sorry.

34:18.866 --> 34:20.824
Well, I do appreciate
you acknowledging

34:20.955 --> 34:23.218
how hard it was on us
when you went away.

34:23.348 --> 34:25.568
Yeah. I'm just sorry
I couldn't provide, that's all.

34:25.699 --> 34:27.222
Lamar, it's not about that.

34:27.352 --> 34:28.571
Look, I only went to see Zo

34:28.702 --> 34:30.704
'cause I wanted
to tell her that.

34:30.834 --> 34:32.880
And when I saw her
run away from me,

34:33.010 --> 34:34.882
it felt like everything
that I fought for

34:35.012 --> 34:37.885
the past two years
was for nothing.

34:39.408 --> 34:41.323
Lamar, honestly,
what do you want?

34:41.454 --> 34:43.281
What--[scoffs]

34:44.935 --> 34:47.111
I want Zoe to know
that I'm her father,

34:47.242 --> 34:49.244
and that I'm there for her.

34:49.374 --> 34:52.073
And when the time is right,

34:52.203 --> 34:53.596
I'd like to see her.

34:54.554 --> 34:56.773
Well, I'll talk to Zoe
and see how she feel about it.

34:56.904 --> 34:58.558
Thanks, and...

35:01.212 --> 35:02.562
-Look, that...
-Hey.

35:02.692 --> 35:04.999
Mo, that is all I ask.

35:05.129 --> 35:06.827
[scoffs]

35:06.957 --> 35:08.655
A'ight.

35:11.745 --> 35:13.268
[Meech] What the fuck, Nicole?

35:13.398 --> 35:14.356
Do you even know
where the hell you were?

35:14.487 --> 35:16.010
-Who cares?
-Who cares?

35:16.140 --> 35:18.273
I told you not
to ever go to Ecorse.

35:18.403 --> 35:20.014
And now you doing it with
everything that's going on?

35:20.144 --> 35:21.145
Do you even know Terry
got rushed back into surgery?

35:21.276 --> 35:22.930
So what?

35:23.060 --> 35:23.844
[Meech] The fuck you talking
about, "So what"?

35:23.974 --> 35:25.106
What's wrong with you?

35:25.236 --> 35:26.760
[dramatic music plays]

35:26.890 --> 35:28.196
[brakes screeching]

35:28.326 --> 35:30.894
[horns blaring]

35:32.287 --> 35:33.114
What the fuck is your problem?

35:33.244 --> 35:34.245
Let me out! Let me out!

35:34.376 --> 35:35.899
Not until you talk to me.

35:36.030 --> 35:38.119
Let me out!

35:38.249 --> 35:40.295
[screams]

35:41.775 --> 35:42.950
I hate you!

35:43.080 --> 35:45.387
[dramatic music plays]

35:45.518 --> 35:46.867
[tires squeal]

35:48.433 --> 35:49.522
[tires squeal]

35:51.567 --> 35:54.352
[boat horn blares softly]

35:56.311 --> 35:58.008
